==Slovak==
===Etymology===
:'''auto-''' (as in ''automotive'') + '''-bus''', the ending of '''omnibus''', Latin meaning ''for all''. In other words, an automobile for public transportation.

===Noun===
:'''autobus''' ''m'', '''autobusy''' ''pl''
:'''autobus''' ''stem''
:'''autobusu''' ''{{gensg}}''
:{{decpat}} {{dub}}
# a large public transportation vehicle with a combustion engine, a [[bus]]

